A middle-aged pedestrian was crushed to death by a speeding vehicle along Awka/Enugu expressway, Anambra state. The crash, which occurred Wednesday evening, involved a brown coloured Toyota Camry Car with registration number AJL 471 DN. According to eyewitness, the driver was on top speed when he lost control and knocked down the pedestrian trying to cross the road. The Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Adeoye Irelewuyi confirmed the incident. He commiserated with the deceased family, warning motorist to avoid speeding and ensure they keep to recommended speed limit. - Advertisement -   Toxic fuel: Was it off spec or contaminated?     IPOB warns against defaming Kanu’s lawyer     Lawyer: Ex-JAMB Registrar Ojerinde shielded firms, assets in…   He said: “Unidentified driver of brown coloured Toyota Camry Car with registration number AJL 471 DN had a lone Fatal road traffic crash at front of UBA Awka by Awka-Enugu expressway, on 9th February, 2022 at about 16:41hrs. “Two male adults were involved in the crash. One of the male adult (the driver) sustained varying degrees of injuries, while a male adult (pedestrian) was killed. “FRSC rescue team from Awka Sector Command rushed the victims to Amaku hospital Awka where a male adult was confirmed dead. The dead victim was deposited at the hospital morgue. “The vehicle involved in the crash was handed over to CPS Police Division while the driver is currently receiving treatment. “FRSC Rescue team on ground managed the traffic and ensured obstruction caused by the crash was removed. “Speeding most time usually causes loss of control and at the end leads to road traffic crash. “Let’s keep our road safe from crash.”